<% content_for :title, "Mushroom Field Notebook and Identification Database" %>
<% content_for :meta_description, "Browse mushroom specimen observations and track identification data, photos, and field notes with MRDBID." %>

<h1>Welcome to MRDBID! MushRoom DataBase IDentification</h1>

<div class="group-box mb-4" style="border: 2px solid #16a34a;">
  <div class="group-header" style="background-color: #dcfce7;">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">MRDBID has evolved into one goal for mushroom enthusiasts. Create an easy-to-use tool for mushroom identification with search capabilities.</h2>

    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">If this tool already exists and is in use, I would love to know about it. If not, I have at least answered the question "OK, you identified the problem; what is your solution?"</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">I have created a simple Google style form input box that will auto-complete as you type in a specific character, such as cap width. I have input a table of characters to use. Some need options which I have in another table. How about a process to add and/or edit these lists? Done.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">I have files for download of the database tables I am using. I have an Excel spreadsheet listing my starting points available for download.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">My goal is to create a table of data for each mushroom consisting of integers that can be easily searched in large numbers to match up mushrooms. Pretty much done except for the implementation.</p>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">If you have this tool. Great! Where is it? If not, what I have is a starting point that the community can fine-tune and improve.</p>

  </div>
  <div class="px-4 py-4">
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">You must register and login for most features of MRDBID. Several tools are open to all visitors — see below.</p>
    <ol class="list-decimal pl-5 space-y-2">
      <li>Mushroom collection organizer and notebook. (This is just a placeholder for now. I envision the <span class="text-orange-600 text-lg sm:ml-2">MUSHROOM IDENTIFICATION WORD LIST</span> tools to be incorporated as a widget in sites like MycoMap, iNaturalist, Mushroom Observer, and others.)</li>
      <li><span class="text-orange-600 text-lg sm:ml-2">MUSHROOM IDENTIFICATION WORD LIST</span> tools for the creation, modification, and use of <em>mushroom</em> characters* in online form.</li>
      <li>DNA sequence index tools with iNaturalist links and genera counts.</li>
      <li>Searchable database of iNaturalist Observation Fields.</li>
      <li>Mycowriter - Rails gem to autocomplete genus species names.</li>
      <li>Auto-Glossary - Rails gem to highlight mycology terms in text linked to Wikipedia's Glossary of Mycology.</li>
    </ol>
    <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">* NOT to be confused with mushroom <span class="text-gray-4 text-sm sm:ml-2">CARTOON</span> <u>characters</u> returned in searches.</p>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Public tools - no login required -->
<div class="group-box mb-4" style="border: 2px solid #2563eb;">
  <div class="group-header" style="background-color: #dbeafe;">
    <h2 class="text-lg font-bold text-gray-900">Open to All Visitors — No Login Required</h2>
  </div>
  <div class="px-4 py-4">
    <ul class="space-y-3">
      <li>
        <%= link_to sighting_schedule_mushrooms_path, class: "group flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline gap-1" do %>
          <span class="font-semibold text-blue-700 group-hover:underline">Fungus Sighting Schedule</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:ml-2">Browse all collection records organized by month to see when fungi appear throughout the year.</span>
        <% end %>
      </li>
      <li>
        <%= link_to mr_characters_path, class: "group flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline gap-1" do %>
          <span class="font-semibold text-blue-700 group-hover:underline">Mushroom Characters Catalog</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:ml-2">Reference list of all observable characteristics — cap, gill, stem, spore, and more — used for identification.</span>
        <% end %>
      </li>
      <li>
        <%= link_to inaturalist_observation_fields_path, class: "group flex flex-col sm:flex-row sm:items-baseline gap-1" do %>
          <span class="font-semibold text-blue-700 group-hover:underline">iNaturalist Observation Fields</span>
          <span class="text-gray-600 text-sm sm:ml-2">Searchable database of all iNaturalist observation fields relevant to fungi and mycology workflows.</span>
        <% end %>
      </li>
    </ul>
  </div>
</div>

<!-- Pagination Top -->
<div class="mb-1">
  <%= render "shared/pagination", collection: @mushrooms %>
</div>

<!-- Mushroom Observation Cards -->
<% if @mushrooms&.any? %>
  <% grouped = @mushrooms.group_by { |m| m.fungus_type&.name.to_s.presence || "Uncategorized" } %>
  <% grouped.keys.sort.each do |ft_name| %>
    <!-- Fungus Type Header -->
    <div class="mb-6">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-800 mb-3 pb-2 border-b-2 border-gray-300">
        <%= ft_name %>
      </h2>

      <!-- 4-column grid of mushrooms -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-3 lg:grid-cols-4 gap-4">
        <% grouped[ft_name].each do |mushroom| %>
          <%= link_to mushroom_path(mushroom), class: "block border-2 border-gray-400 rounded-lg overflow-hidden bg-white hover:shadow-lg transition" do %>
            <!-- Image -->
            <% images = mushroom.image_mushrooms.select { |im| im.image_file.attached? } %>
            <% if images.any? %>
              <div class="relative w-full" style="height: 200px;">
                <%= image_tag(
                      url_for(images.first.image_file.variant(
                        resize_to_fill: [300, 300],
                        format: :webp,
                        saver: { strip: true, quality: 70, effort: 4 }
                      )),
                      alt: mushroom.name || "Mushroom image",
                      class: "w-full h-full object-cover",
                      onerror: "this.style.display='none'; this.parentElement.innerHTML='<div class=\\'w-full h-full bg-gray-200 flex items-center justify-center\\'><span class=\\'text-gray-400 text-sm\\'>Image unavailable</span></div>';"
                    ) %>
                <% if images.size > 1 %>
                  <span class="absolute top-2 right-2 bg-black bg-opacity-70 text-white text-xs px-2 py-1 rounded">
                    +<%= images.size - 1 %>
                  </span>
                <% end %>
              </div>
            <% else %>
              <!-- Placeholder if no image -->
              <div class="w-full bg-gray-200 flex items-center justify-center" style="height: 200px;">
                <span class="text-gray-400 text-sm">No image</span>
              </div>
            <% end %>

            <!-- Text content below image -->
            <div class="p-3">
              <% identifications = mushroom.ranked_identifications %>
              <% if identifications.any? %>
                <div class="text-xs italic text-gray-600 mb-1">
                  <em><%= identifications.first[:genus]&.name&.capitalize || '?' %> <%= identifications.first[:species]&.name || '?' %></em>
                </div>
              <% end %>

              <p class="font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-1">
                <%= mushroom.name.presence || "Unnamed" %>
              </p>

              <% if mushroom.collection_date.present? %>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-600">
                  <%= mushroom.collection_date.strftime('%m-%d-%Y') %>
                </p>
              <% end %>

              <% location_parts = [
                mushroom.city,
                (mushroom.county.present? ? "#{mushroom.county} County" : nil),
                mushroom.state&.name,
                mushroom.country&.name
              ].compact.reject(&:blank?) %>
              <% if location_parts.any? %>
                <p class="text-xs text-gray-500">
                  <%= location_parts.join(", ") %>
                </p>
              <% end %>
            </div>
          <% end %>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>
  <% end %>
<% else %>
  <p class="text-center text-gray-600 my-8">No mushrooms available.</p>
<% end %>

<!-- Pagination Bottom -->
<div class="mt-2">
  <%= render "shared/pagination", collection: @mushrooms %>
</div>

<section class="mt-10 space-y-6">
  <div class="border-t border-gray-300 pt-6">
    <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Background and Project Direction</h2>
    <div class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
      <%= render template: "pages/home_EXD" %>
    </div>
  </div>

  <% if @home_short_articles.any? %>
    <div class="border-t border-gray-300 pt-6">
      <h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">Additional Notes and Updates</h2>
      <div class="space-y-8">
        <% @home_short_articles.each do |article| %>
          <article class="bg-white border border-gray-200 rounded-lg p-4">
            <h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900"><%= sanitize(article.title, tags: %w[em i]) %></h3>
            <div class="mt-3 prose max-w-none">
              <% if article.body.to_s.strip.starts_with?("<") %>
                <%= raw mark_glossary_terms(sanitize(article.body,
                    tags: %w[div p span br ul ol li h2 h3 h4 strong em a blockquote code pre img table thead tbody tr th td b u i],
                    attributes: %w[href src alt title class style])) %>
              <% else %>
                <%= raw mark_glossary_terms(simple_format(article.body)) %>
              <% end %>
            </div>
          </article>
        <% end %>
      </div>
    </div>
  <% end %>
</section>
